Product Description

UGREEN Active HDMI to VGA Adapter with 3.5mm Audio HDMI Female to VGA Male Converter

HDMI Female to VGA Male adapter

The HDMI to VGA converter is a portable digital-analog conversion adapter, enables you to connect an HDMI output device, such as a laptop video output or digital media extender to a VGA display device (monitor, projector) by converting the HDMI video signal from the output device into a VGA output. Plug and play, easy to use,a perfect companion for an easy and enjoying life!

Compatible device

HDMI to VGA adapter are widely used with HDMI input source HDMI source: Desktop/Notebook/Fire Stick/Nintendo Switch/Raspberry Pi/Tablet PC/Digital Set-top Box/ Digital Camera/SLR Camera/Video Camera and other equipment through this adapter connected

Specification

HDMI video input formats: 480i / 576i / 480p / 576p / 720p / 1080i / 1080p

VGA video output formats: 480i / 576i / 480p / 576p / 720p / 1080i / 1080p

Products for audio output: 3.5 Audio /3.5 TO R + L

Product inputs: HDMI

Product output terminal: VGA + Audio

Micro usb port for additional power supply

Note:

1.It couldn't convert VGA to HDMI, it is not bidirectional

2.Please use HDMI version 1.4 cable within 8 meters to ensure the high performance of this item.

Package include:

1 x HDMI to VGA Adapter

1 x Micro usb cable

Mini DP to HDMI VGA Adapter Mini DP to HDMI VGA Adapter HDMI to VGA Adapter with 3.5mm Audio Jack Mini DP to HDMI Adapter Mini DP to HDMI DVI VGA Adapter
Converter Mini DP Male to HDMI & VGA Female Mini DP to HDMI & VGA HDMI Male to VGA Female Mini DP Male to HDMI Female Mini DP Male to HDMI DVI VGA Female
Resolution 4K@30Hz 4K@30Hz 1080P@60Hz 1080P 4K@30Hz
Color White Black Black White Black
Material PVC PVC PVC PVC PVC

      Derek Green
      5.0 out of 5 stars Works great with Raspberry Pie/Retro Pie setup
      Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2019
      Verified Purchase
      Works great with my Retro Pie setup! Getting a crisp picture on my 1080 monitor took some digging. Here are the steps:
      1.) Make sure you use the included USB cable and plug that into your Pie (or anywhere that has power, but Pie was easy)
      2.) SSH into your Pie using Putty or the like
      3.) Run the command "sudo nano /boot/config.txt"
      4.) Now that you're in the config, delete the # in front of the lines for "hdmi_group" and "hdmi_mode"
      5.) Set hdmi_group = 82
      6.) Save the file by hitting ctrl+O and then exit with ctrl+X
      7.) Restart Pie

      This works with my 1080p HD monitor, your results may vary. Have fun!

      Amazon Customer
      4.0 out of 5 stars It Works! .... eventually
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 25, 2017
      Verified Purchase
      Used for Amazon Fire TV Stick to a 2004 Philips 24inch flat screen with no HDMI but with VGA input. I thought I was going to have to send this back as all I got was lines across the screen when I first connected the adapter. After a bit of investigating online I found the screen resolution setting needed for the TV was different to the setting for my newer living room TV.

      I put the Fire Stick back into my living room TV and on the Fire Stick went to 'Settings', 'Display & Sounds', 'Video Resolution' and changed it from 'Auto' to '720p 60Hz' (picture attached)

      I then connected the Fire Stick to the adapter put it back in the old Philips TV and it worked perfectly this time. I connected my portable JAM speaker to the adapter and the sound was good and in sync. Woohoo :-) I can now watch Amazon Prime, Netflix and BBC iPlayer etc in the bedroom now without having to buy a new TV.

      I knocked a star off the review as it would have been good to have some helpful instructions in the box with some troubleshooting tips.
